<br>
&quot;Beginners use Napalm&quot;<br>
by: Rick G.<br>
Team C.O.R.E. (The Connecticut Order of Raging Egomaniacs)<br>
   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Grega:<br>
The only starting card useful to this deck is the Arbolit. The others just don&#39;t fit the Direct Damage plan. With Grega, you want to focus on playing mostly creatures. Save your damaging spells for your next Magi. Each turn, as long as you have creatures in play, use her Thermal Blast on something. Try to target a creature with the exact ammount (Or as close to it) so you don&#39;t waste the Thermal Blast. For Example, if your opponent has a 5 and a 3 energy creature in play, and for Thermal Blast you roll a 6, target the 5 energy creature to get rid of it. This is the most effective way to use Grega. Utilize her ability to take away your opponents with creatures and powers. Once again, save your spells for Valkan. If you get two, play a Water of Life also, if you only draw one with Grega, save it for Valkan because he needs the extra energy.<br>
<br>
Valkan:<br>
Valkan is a fiery little midgit from the land of flame. With him, the ideal things to get out would be a Scroll of Fire, Water of Life, and at least 1 Giant Arboll in play. When you cast your spells, the Giant Arboll gains 1 energy. Each spell you cast that removes energy from one of your opponents creatures in play. This way, a Thermal Blast for which your roll a 6, would remove 8 from a creature. Your Lava Flows still remove only 2 energy, but your Fire Balls and Firefly Swarm will remove 4 from each creature they hit. Try to keep a couple of creatures in your hand for yout next Magi Gar.<br>
<br>
Gar: <br>
When Gar comes up, you need to be agressive and play a lot of creatures. Once you get the ranks of Dream Creautures in play, attack with them so you get to add energy to them at the end of the turn. Gar is the Caldrean Healer, so you should probably try to amass an army of Creatures including at least one Eargar to totally sap your opponents energy away, then heal the lowest creature at the end of the turn.<br>
<br>
This deck is simple enough to play and there are not any combos really, just destroy the opponent with your Creatures (Gregar and Gar) and your Spells (Valkan).<br>
<br>
Good Luck and I hope the deck works out for you... </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
